init_text:
What Stereotypical Characters Make You Cringe?

What stereotypical characters in books, movies or television shows make you cringe and why? Would you ever not watch or read something because of its offensive portrayal of someone?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Instead of laughing, I began feeling uncomfortable and uncertain that I wanted to watch that program anymore.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: What will be my tipping point for comedy?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The example that comes to mind is "cracking" on someone's weight.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I now see it as hurtful, and I really don't know how some people continue to laugh at that, because it no longer seems very funny

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's a combination of the portrayal and the circumstances.
